      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "msg_b67c40b4-676d-49c8-93a8-d8f658ba024c",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "I've been feeling anxious lately",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:39:47.356Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_c8f54949-f1a7-4f88-b236-5612682b34a5",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "If your thoughts are looping, try a “name it to tame it” moment: label what’s happening (e.g., “I’m having an anxious thought”), then ask, “What would I tell a friend in this situation?” We can take it one piece at a time.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:39:47.360Z"
        }
      ],
      "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:39:47.349Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-25T11:39:47.360Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "chat_91219454-b961-49f1-96e2-668058097f32",
      "userId": "usr_0968d1ee-2b61-4970-a407-37d233fbe52b",
      "title": "I'm having trouble sleeping",
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "msg_cccad9aa-0e29-4d68-b547-7eee9dc77dab",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "I'm having trouble sleeping",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:40:03.234Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_e3606fa3-7165-4525-a3e3-2602b8b6a938",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "If you’re awake and frustrated, it can help to stop “trying” to sleep. Try a low-light reset: sit up, read something boring, or do a body scan for 5–10 minutes, then return to bed when you feel drowsy again.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:40:03.235Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_e363883a-2411-4fb1-b7ac-6730ecd8c27f",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Body scan",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-25T11:40:09.721Z"
